<div class="container">
    <h1>Types of Frontend Technologies</h1>
    <p>Now that you know what the frontend is, let’s look at some of the tools and technologies used to build the things we see and use on a website or app.</p>

    <h2>1. HTML (HyperText Markup Language)</h2>
    <p>This is the basic building block of any webpage. It tells the browser what to show – like text, images, and links.</p>
    <p><strong>Use for:</strong> Creating the structure of the page.</p>

    <h2>2. CSS (Cascading Style Sheets)</h2>
    <p>CSS makes everything look nice! It changes the colors, fonts, layout, and animations of the page.</p>
    <p><strong>Use for:</strong> Styling and making the page beautiful and fun.</p>

    <h2>3. JavaScript</h2>
    <p>This is the magic behind interactions. It lets you click buttons, show pop-ups, and update the page without reloading.</p>
    <p><strong>Use for:</strong> Making the page dynamic and interactive.</p>

    <h2>4. Frontend Frameworks</h2>
    <p>These are special tools that help developers build websites faster and more easily. Examples include:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>React.js</li>
        <li>Angular</li>
        <li>Vue.js</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Use for:</strong> Creating large, interactive web apps more efficiently.</p>

    <h2>5. Responsive Design Tools</h2>
    <p>These help make sure the website works well on phones, tablets, and computers. Tools like Bootstrap or Tailwind CSS help with this.</p>
    <p><strong>Use for:</strong> Making the website look good on all screen sizes.</p>

